1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:05,000
RAPTOR. Real-time aerial persistent thermal object reasoning.

2
00:00:05,123 --> 00:00:15,123
MARADMIN 131/26 calls for digital tools to enhance situational awareness during installation-level incidents.

3
00:00:15,156 --> 00:00:25,156
We pull from HIT-UAV — high-altitude infrared thermal imagery. 30 frames, 640 by 512, no data movement.

4
00:00:18,229 --> 00:00:28,229
Heuristic blob detection finds heat signatures in under 30 milliseconds. Persons, vehicles, fires, generators — classified live.

5
00:00:23,537 --> 00:00:48,537
A Kamiwaza-deployed vision-language model reads the current frame plus five prior frames and writes a four-paragraph mission INTREP. Multi-step reasoning across a temporal window, on-prem.

6
00:00:48,065 --> 00:01:03,065
Structured JSON drops straight into a COC dispatch ticket. An E-5 watchstander gets an actionable answer in under ten seconds.

7
00:01:02,390 --> 00:01:12,390
Set KAMIWAZA_BASE_URL and KAMIWAZA_API_KEY — same code, now behind the wire. 100% data containment. SIPR and JWICS ready.

8
00:01:12,394 --> 00:01:17,394
RAPTOR. Powered by a Kamiwaza-deployed model. Deploy in hours, not months.
